1. Clear presentation of findings (1 point): The conclusion clearly summarizes the results of each exercise, providing a brief overview of the experiments conducted and their outcomes.
2. Interpretation of results (1 point): The student demonstrates an understanding of the significance of the findings by interpreting the results of each exercise in relation to the exercise's objective.
3. Identification of limitations (1 point): The student identifies any limitations or assumptions made during the analysis and acknowledges their potential impact on the results.
4. Implications for security (1 point): The student discusses the implications of the findings for file permissions, user access, and security in Linux operating systems, highlighting the practical relevance of their investigation.
5. Recommendations for future work (1 point): The student provides suggestions for future research or improvements based on the findings, demonstrating an understanding of the broader context and potential applications of their work.